		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://brickisland.net/cs177fa12/?p=320#comment-65</guid>
		<description>It may be useful to know that there is a method &lt;tt&gt;inner( x, B, y )&lt;/tt&gt; (declared in &lt;tt&gt;DenseMatrix.h&lt;/tt&gt;) which evaluates the inner product with respect to a given matrix $B$.  Using this routine, you should be able to implement the routines &lt;tt&gt;IsometricWillmoreFlow1D::orthogonalizeConstraints()&lt;/tt&gt; and &lt;tt&gt;IsometricWillmoreFlow1D::enforceConstraints()&lt;/tt&gt; with a &lt;em&gt;very&lt;/em&gt; small number of lines of code -- something like eight lines for the former and three lines for the latter (depending on your indentation style!).</description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>It may be useful to know that there is a method <tt>inner( x, B, y )</tt> (declared in <tt>DenseMatrix.h</tt>) which evaluates the inner product with respect to a given matrix $B$.  Using this routine, you should be able to implement the routines <tt>IsometricWillmoreFlow1D::orthogonalizeConstraints()</tt> and <tt>IsometricWillmoreFlow1D::enforceConstraints()</tt> with a <em>very</em> small number of lines of code &#8212; something like eight lines for the former and three lines for the latter (depending on your indentation style!).</p>
]]></content:encoded>
